40|$|Microcalorimeter <b>X-ray</b> <b>detectors</b> using a {{transition}} edge sensor depend for their linearity and energy scale on {{the stability of}} the operating point on the transition curve. We report on some sources of energy scale drift in microcalorimeter <b>X-ray</b> <b>detectors</b> {{and the manner in which}} they have been addressed. Previously observed drifts of> 10 eV/h have been reduced to 1 - 2 eV/h. This improved stability has resulted in the observation of X-ray fluorescence linewidths of ≤ 12 eV over 6 h of counting time...|$|R
